'''Ōtorii Ōji''' is one of the {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|fr|Kujūku Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=99 ōji Shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft}} on the [[Kumano Kodō]].
==Overview== {{Shrine | Name = {{ill|Ōtorii Ōji|ja|大鳥居王子|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | image = | location = {{ill|Nishi-ku, Sakai|ja|堺市西区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Sakai, Osaka|ja|堺市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Japan | coordinates = | deity = | Affiliation = {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - {{ill|Kumano Pilgrimage|ja|熊野信仰|1=Kumano Three Shrines|lt=Kumano faith|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | Established = {{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (around 1201) | Map = }}
'''{{ill|Ōtorii Ōji|ja|大鳥居王子|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' (おおとりいおうじ), also known as '''{{ill|Ōtori Ōji|ja|大鳥王子|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''', was the 8th of the {{ill|Kumano Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|qq=draft|qq=draft}} shrines along the historic {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|qq=draft|qq=draft}} pilgrimage route, counting from the starting point at {{ill|Kubotsu Ōji|ja|窪津王子|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== History == The existence of Ōtorii Ōji is documented in the 1201 ({{ill|Kennin era|ja|建仁|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 1) record of Emperor {{ill|Go-Toba|ja|後鳥羽天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'s pilgrimage to Kumano, titled *{{ill|Go-Toba-in Kumano Gyokō-ki|ja|後鳥羽院熊野御幸記|qq=draft|qq=draft}}*, where it is referred to as "Ōtorii Shin Ōji" (大鳥居新王子). This suggests that the shrine was established relatively close to that period.
The name "Ōtorii" (meaning "Great Torii Gate") is believed to originate from its association with the nearby {{ill|Ōtori Shrine|ja|大鳥大社|1=Ōtori taisha|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and its prominent torii gate.
== location == Ōtorii Ōji was located in the historical {{ill|Ōtori District, Izumi|ja|大鳥郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'s Kita-Ōji Village, believed to correspond to the current area around the {{ill|NTT Ōtori Office|ja|NTT鳳営業所|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Ōtori Higashi-chō|ja|鳳東町|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 7-chōme, {{ill|Nishi-ku, Sakai|ja|堺市西区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
It is also associated with the {{ill|Ōtori Minabehi Shrine|ja|大鳥美波比神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, which was relocated in 1879 ({{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 12) to the grounds of Ōtori Shrine.
== Access == * '''{{ill|Ōtori Station|ja|鳳駅|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' on the {{ill|Hanwa Line|ja|阪和線|qq=draft|qq=draft}} operated by {{ill|JR West|ja|西日本旅客鉄道|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== See also == * {{ill|Kumano Sanzan|ja|熊野三山|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - {{ill|Kiiji|ja|紀伊路|1=Kiiji|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Kumano Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|qq=draft|qq=draft}} *: {{ill|Sakai Ōji|ja|境王子|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * '''{{ill|Ōtorii Ōji|ja|大鳥居王子|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' - {{ill|Shinoda Ōji|ja|篠田王子|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
